pageContext.claim: “African American unemployment, Asian unemployment, Hispanic unemployment is at record lows in history -- not, you know, for the last two years -- the history of our country.”
pageContext.analysis: The Asian-American statistic has been around for less than 20 years. And while it reached a low of 2.1 percent rate in May 2018, it returned to 3.1 percent in July, the most recent month available.
